.TH "scsi_add_single_device" 9 "scsi_add_single_device" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
scsi_add_single_device \- Respond to user request to probe for/add device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" scsi_add_single_device
.BI "(uint host "  ","
.BI "uint channel "  ","
.BI "uint id "  ","
.BI "uint lun "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "host" 12
user-supplied decimal integer
.IP "channel" 12
user-supplied decimal integer
.IP "id" 12
user-supplied decimal integer
.IP "lun" 12
user-supplied decimal integer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
called by writing "scsi add-single-device" to /proc/scsi/scsi.

does \fBscsi_host_lookup\fP and either \fBuser_scan\fP if that transport
type supports it, or else \fBscsi_scan_host_selected\fP
.SH "NOTE"
this seems to be aimed exclusively at SCSI parallel busses.
